    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Materials-related distress arising from a simple acid-base reaction between alkali hydroxyl ions in portland cement and siliceous minerals. Found in many aggregates, it results in premature deterioration of concrete structures including bridges, dams, and pavements.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
